narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: Intro to the language and learn a lot about how it works.
This course taught fundamentals of Czech grammar, and likewise developed skills in comprehension and speaking.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: Really engages the class. Also answers the question very well and gives good examples.

I think this class was organized very well, and I found classes to be engaging! I do have a suggestion though- when we reached adjectives in the plural, I felt like we still hadn't really internalized adjectives in the singular. We did practice using jak to determine adjectival endings, but I think we should have practiced more figuring out adjectives without the help of jak (e.g, inserting adjectives into short sentences in all cases). It wouldn't take much since it follows very easily from ten/ta/to, and internalizing it would have helped with plural. Also, a general note is I found worksheets to be very helpful overall.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: KvK is wonderful! Czech has been a very enjoyable class, and I feel like I am actually learning the language. Our class was just 5 people, which I very much appreciated. While it is not too much work to just get by in this class, if you take it I highly recommend you take learning the language seriously.
